- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the management of unmanned-aerial-vehicle traffic, which involves control and coordination of multiple systems. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not a major focus of the paper, the use of unmanned-aerial-vehicles raises security concerns that may be addressed in this sub-category. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The proposed use of pre-established route networks and mapping of obstacles suggests the involvement of software engineering techniques.
